1 SECTION 2.4. The Department of Health and Human Services shall adopt or
2 amend any rules, policies, or procedures necessary to give effect to Sections 2.1 and 2.2 of this
3 act.
4 SECTION 2.5. Sections 2.1 and 2.2 of this act become effective July 1, 2026, and
5 apply to net proceeds credited on or after that date. Section 2.3 of this act becomes effective July
6 1, 2026.
7
8 PART III. PLAN FOR IMPLEMENTATION OF STATEWIDE FLOOR
9 SECTION 3. The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Child
10 Development and Early Education (Division), shall develop a plan for implementing a statewide
11 child care subsidy reimbursement rate floor. The Division shall submit a report with their
12 recommended plan no later than December 1, 2026 to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee
13 on Health and Human Services and the Fiscal Research Division.
14
15 PART IV. EFFECTIVE DATE
16 SECTION 4. Except as otherwise provided, this act becomes effective when it
17 becomes law.
